00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:15,180
Stop thinking about it. You can't blame yourself for this.

259
00:19:15,180 --> 00:19:18,200
All right, let's not think about it anymore.

260
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,940
Okay?

261
00:19:20,940 --> 00:19:25,590

262
00:19:26,260 --> 00:19:28,380
Just pay attention to her diet and daily routines.

263
00:19:28,380 --> 00:19:33,100
And this patient likes to eat spicy food, so advise her to avoid it.

264
00:19:33,100 --> 00:19:34,180
Okay.

265
00:19:34,180 --> 00:19:36,660
There's nothing else, so you can go now.

266
00:19:56,040 --> 00:19:59,480
You must be exhausted these days.

267
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,140
I'm fine.

268
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:06,180
Seeing you like this,

269
00:20:07,043 --> 00:20:10,480
you must've been through a lot of worries and fears, running around here and there.

270
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:14,380
I'm okay. It's just that my aunt suffered a lot.

271
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:15,860
How is she doing now?

272
00:20:15,860 --> 00:20:17,260
She's much better.

273
00:20:17,260 --> 00:20:20,780
She's been transferred to another ward for further observation.

274
00:20:20,780 --> 00:20:22,480
That's good.

275
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:25,780
You...

276
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:31,960
Why did you keep the phone number you used in Lakaya?

277
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:41,380
I'm afraid the doctors in Lakaya will need remote assistance.

278
00:20:44,295 --> 00:20:47,700
I'm just kidding, silly.

279
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:49,840
I'm afraid you won't be able to find me.

280
00:20:57,100 --> 00:20:59,420
Actually, for these past few days...

281
00:21:01,060 --> 00:21:04,180
I've been looking for a chance to apologize to you.

282
00:21:04,180 --> 00:21:05,740
I'm sorry.

283
00:21:05,740 --> 00:21:08,780
I think your suspicions about HDQ39 might be correct.

284
00:21:08,780 --> 00:21:14,280
If I had listened to you back then, even if it was just suspicions,

285
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:20,540
and asked my aunt to temporarily stop the medication, maybe we wouldn't be in this situation now.

286
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:29,560
Right, I... can I ask you for a favor?

287
00:21:30,280 --> 00:21:32,520
Can you help me find out

288
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:38,020
if HDQ39 really cause aneurysms?

289
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:40,700
Su Wei'an,

290
00:21:41,580 --> 00:21:43,960
why don't you look into it yourself?

291
00:21:45,940 --> 00:21:47,620
I...

292
00:21:47,620 --> 00:21:49,220
You also studied medicine.

293
00:21:49,220 --> 00:21:52,480
What I can do, you can do as well.

294
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:54,500
I'm just an undergraduate. I can't.

295
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:57,540
You haven't even tried. How do you know you can't?

296
00:21:57,540 --> 00:22:02,240
Professor Lu also said that you have outstanding medical talents and gifts.

297
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:04,400
Why do you want to waste them?

298
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:06,780
I really can't do it.

299
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:13,420
You're more likely to uncover the truth than I am. You're Gu Yunzheng.

300
00:22:13,420 --> 00:22:15,460
But I'm not you.

301
00:22:16,580 --> 00:22:21,420
Su Wei'an, only you can resolve your inner obstacles.

302
00:22:27,220 --> 00:22:31,120
I don't have time. I still need to take care of my mom and my aunt.

303
00:22:31,120 --> 00:22:34,860
I still need to make money. I still have a lot to do.

304
00:22:38,260 --> 00:22:41,800
No. Su Wei'an,

305
00:22:42,380 --> 00:22:44,560
you're afraid.

306
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:48,560
Back in Lakaya, didn't you already try recklessly

307
00:22:48,560 --> 00:22:53,040
to follow Eliot to France to participate in medical research experiments?

308
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:59,740
- How did you know? 
 - Why did you dare to do it back then, but not now?

309
00:23:00,360 --> 00:23:02,240
Because...

310
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:05,280
Because I was stubborn and already got my aunt into trouble.

311
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:14,460
Even if there's only the slightest chance, we should still try our best.

312
00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:17,620
This is the instinct of every medical student.

313
00:23:21,060 --> 00:23:23,860
Su Wei'an, you're not doing this for yourself.

314
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:31,680
Participating in the drug trial wasn't just for my aunt's illness.

315
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:37,560
Because I also carry the chorea gene.

316
00:23:40,120 --> 00:23:44,900
So, I particularly hope that HDQ39 can be put on the market.

317
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:50,880
I'm not trustworthy at all, and I don't deserve to participate in medical research.

318
00:23:55,860 --> 00:23:58,140
Su Wei'an, you're right.

319
00:23:58,140 --> 00:24:01,060
You're extremely selfish and despicable.

320
00:24:01,060 --> 00:24:06,100
You knew that participating in the drug trial could potentially lead to a serious aneurysm rupture,

321
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:10,620
but you still treated your aunt like a guinea pig and forced her to participate.

322
00:24:10,620 --> 00:24:12,425
Is that right?

323
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:35,850
Since you didn't do that,

324
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:41,550
what exactly did you do wrong that you are tormenting yourself like this?

325
00:24:41,550 --> 00:24:46,040
If it's not my fault, then whose fault is it?

326
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:53,520
Every time I have the tiniest bit of hope,

327
00:24:54,550 --> 00:24:57,570
all I end up with is despair.

328
00:24:58,520 --> 00:25:01,620
Why does misfortune have to befall me?

329
00:25:01,620 --> 00:25:08,800
Why did such a rare and unlikely disease strike my family with such precision, like a bolt of lightning?

330
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:13,280
Why must there be cursed people like us in this world?

331
00:25:39,960 --> 00:25:41,465
Hello, Wei'an.

332
00:25:41,465 --> 00:25:46,090
 Senior, I've decided not to go to Jiehui.

333
00:25:46,090 --> 00:25:48,595
Why? Is it because of the salary?

334
00:25:48,595 --> 00:25:51,240
 Regarding my aunt's aneurysm rupture this time,

335
00:25:51,240 --> 00:25:53,880
I think Gu Yunzheng's speculations might be right.

336
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:57,470
 It's very likely related to HDQ39.

337
00:25:58,240 --> 00:25:59,638
 As a patient's family member,

338
00:25:59,638 --> 00:26:02,623
I shouldn't have any more conflicts of interest with Jiehui.

339
00:26:02,623 --> 00:26:04,320
It doesn't comply with regulations.

340
00:26:04,320 --> 00:26:07,940
 Also, I'd like to ask for your help in confirming whether the drug trial team

341
00:26:07,940 --> 00:26:13,800
 has reported the relevant situation to the Drug Trial Supervisory Department and the Ethics Committee.

342
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:16,940
 They can decide if the drug trial needs to be suspended.

343
00:26:16,940 --> 00:26:22,780
And can the trial team also conduct some studies to clarify whether HDQ39 is related to the formation of aneurysms?

344
00:26:22,780 --> 00:26:24,885
I understand.

345
00:26:24,885 --> 00:26:27,145
I respect your decision.

346
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:32,925
If there's anything else you need help with later on, just let me know.

347
00:26:32,925 --> 00:26:35,090
 Thank you, Senior.

348
00:27:07,770 --> 00:27:09,500

349
00:27:09,500 --> 00:27:14,580
 Dr. Gu, I have a new target now, so I won't pester you anymore.

350
00:27:14,580 --> 00:27:18,670
 However, the collaboration between our two departments will continue.

351
00:27:18,670 --> 00:27:23,520
 I can see that your love has put a lot of pressure on Su Wei'an,

352
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:25,860
 so here's a friendly tip.

353
00:27:25,860 --> 00:27:31,640
 Doting on your partner in every way and giving your all may not necessarily be appreciated.

354
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:36,900
 When you stop being so pushy and act indifferent towards her instead,

355
00:27:36,900 --> 00:27:42,160
 she'll be the one chasing you. In psychology, this is called the Veblen effect.

356
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:44,180
 Good luck!

357
00:27:46,660 --> 00:27:48,120
 Wei'an,

358
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:52,860
 if you refuse to get close to me, then I'll just fly around you.

359
00:28:03,160 --> 00:28:08,880
Jiang Muying. Regarding Su Wei'an's situation, I know everything you know.

360
00:28:08,880 --> 00:28:12,940
I love her, no matter the circumstances.

361
00:28:12,940 --> 00:28:18,660
From the moment I fell for her, I never thought about giving up.

362
00:28:18,660 --> 00:28:22,940
So, as long as Su Wei'an does love me,

363
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:27,840
and as long as you really want what's best for her, just do as I say.

364
00:28:31,672 --> 00:28:35,900
♪  Rain falls on the deep blue sea  ♪

365
00:28:35,900 --> 00:28:41,100
♪  Yet another wave, how many more are coming?  ♪

366
00:28:41,100 --> 00:28:45,620
♪  Love, like a moth, risking it all  ♪

367
00:28:45,620 --> 00:28:47,060

368
00:28:47,060 --> 00:28:53,070
♪  Willing to sacrifice itself for the light  ♪

369
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:59,666
♪  In the endless night, a small fire can be mistaken for a star  ♪

370
00:28:59,666 --> 00:29:04,860
♪  The purity of a single moment can illuminate—  ♪

371
00:29:08,560 --> 00:29:11,920
Professor Wang. Hello, this is Su Wei'an.

372
00:29:12,780 --> 00:29:16,660
Well... please send me the schedule for the French conversation classes.

373
00:29:16,660 --> 00:29:18,920
It's fine to schedule more classes.

374
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:24,180
The price is as we agreed before, 400 RMB per class, right? 
  (56.35 USD)

375
00:29:26,300 --> 00:29:28,540
Okay, thank you.

376
00:29:32,380 --> 00:29:33,840
Stop.

377
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:38,160
Why aren't you going to the interview for that French translator job I recommended?

378
00:29:38,940 --> 00:29:41,320
100,000 RMB a month? How can there be such a good thing? 
  (14,088 USD)

379
00:29:41,320 --> 00:29:43,580
There must be a scam.

380
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:53,560
Is the recruiter male or female?

381
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:55,360
Male.

382
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:58,260
What's wrong with a male?

383
00:29:58,260 --> 00:30:02,420
You... You're being sexist. You only translate for women?

384
00:30:03,660 --> 00:30:07,440
There's no free lunch.

385
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:14,920
- Where are you going? 
 - Restroom.

386
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:17,660
Hello, Dr. Gu.

387
00:30:17,660 --> 00:30:23,100
Wei'an... she absolutely refuses to believe that it's true.

388
00:30:23,100 --> 00:30:26,360
It seems like your idea isn't working.

389
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:33,620
Is that really a good idea?

390
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:38,860
Okay. Okay, sure.

391
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:55,880
I'll tell you the truth.

392
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:59,890
This job comes with conditions.

393
00:31:00,520 --> 00:31:03,040
See? What did I tell you?

394
00:31:05,060 --> 00:31:07,280
Come on, did you really think I'd sell you out?

395
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:11,880
This is a serious translation job. It's going to be published in The Lancet.

396
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:15,620
The Lancet?

397
00:31:18,140 --> 00:31:19,800
But that doesn't make sense.

398
00:31:19,800 --> 00:31:25,300
If it can already be published in such an authoritative journal, why would they need to find another translator?

399
00:31:26,600 --> 00:31:29,960
Because there are tight deadlines, a heavy workload, and high demands.

400
00:31:29,960 --> 00:31:33,160
The content of this job is strictly confidential.

401
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:39,480
Plus, they have to interview candidates first before hiring. That's why the pay is so high.

402
00:31:41,100 --> 00:31:42,800
I think making money is one aspect,

403
00:31:42,800 --> 00:31:46,740
but the most important thing is the opportunity to translate articles at this level.

404
00:31:46,740 --> 00:31:48,900
- When's the interview? 
 - They said

405
00:31:48,900 --> 00:31:53,100
that you must sign this non-disclosure agreement before they can schedule the interview.

406
00:31:57,700 --> 00:31:59,400
Sure.

407
00:32:00,260 --> 00:32:02,420
I'll take this job.

408
00:32:02,420 --> 00:32:04,180
Okay.

409
00:32:04,180 --> 00:32:06,120
Where do I go to start?

410
00:32:15,580 --> 00:32:19,000

411
00:32:35,240 --> 00:32:37,100
Hello? What's the matter?

412
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:39,300
 Don't just stand stupidly at the entrance. Hurry and go in.

413
00:32:39,300 --> 00:32:41,540
 The interview is about to start.

414
00:32:43,300 --> 00:32:45,560
Jiang Muying, are you spying on me?

415
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:47,720
No one knows you better than I do.

416
00:32:47,720 --> 00:32:51,240
Su Wei'an, you only dropped out of school. It's not like you dropped out of life.

417
00:32:51,240 --> 00:32:53,400
Just walk back in there with your head held high.

418
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:55,320
 I'll be waiting for your good news!

419
00:32:55,320 --> 00:32:57,420
All right.

420
00:32:57,420 --> 00:33:03,720

421
00:33:07,300 --> 00:33:11,600
 The treatment for gliomas is mainly surgical intervention.

422
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:14,420
 However, due to the invasive growth of the tumor,

423
00:33:14,420 --> 00:33:19,420
and the lack of clear boundaries between the tumor and brain tissue, it is difficult to resect it completely.

424
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:23,620
 Jiang Muying, just you wait.

425
00:33:23,620 --> 00:33:26,480
That classmate who arrived just before the end of class.

426
00:33:26,480 --> 00:33:29,400
You'll answer my last question.

427
00:33:31,900 --> 00:33:34,380
Sorry, Professor. I'm not from your class.

428
00:33:34,380 --> 00:33:38,280
Student Su Wei'an, I know you.

429
00:33:38,280 --> 00:33:40,360
Your name is on the roster.

430
00:33:40,360 --> 00:33:43,880
If you don't have the handout, you can borrow your classmate's.

431
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:47,520
If you can't answer the question, you can just say you don't know.

432
00:33:47,520 --> 00:33:49,480
At most, this shows your insufficient learning ability,

433
00:33:49,480 --> 00:33:54,920
but deceiving the teacher is a matter of improper attitude.

434
00:33:57,020 --> 00:34:00,020
Okay, Professor. Could you please repeat your question?

435
00:34:00,020 --> 00:34:02,900
How do mutations in IDH  (isocitrate dehydrogenase)  occur?

436
00:34:02,900 --> 00:34:05,300
In most cases, they occur in a mutually exclusive manner.

437
00:34:05,300 --> 00:34:09,980
In gliomas, how do mutations in IDH impact the prognosis of patients?

438
00:34:09,980 --> 00:34:14,320
Mutations in IDH can significantly increase the median survival time of high-grade gliomas,

439
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:18,480
and may predict the chemotherapy sensitivity of both low-grade and secondary high-grade gliomas.

440
00:34:18,480 --> 00:34:21,280
It is associated with improved patient survival rates.

441
00:34:29,220 --> 00:34:30,820
Very good.

442
00:34:32,180 --> 00:34:35,420
Student Su's answer is perfect.

443
00:34:35,420 --> 00:34:39,120
But since you arrived late, I'll still deduct points from your usual grades.

444
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:41,520
Student Su, don't let this happen again.

445
00:34:41,520 --> 00:34:45,420
I also hope that all students here will take this as a warning.

446
00:34:45,420 --> 00:34:46,820
Class dismissed.

447
00:34:46,820 --> 00:34:49,540
 Deduct from what usual grades?

448
00:34:49,540 --> 00:34:52,660
 Gu Yunzheng, you're such a drama queen.

449
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:58,100
Su Wei'an. Su Wei'an!

450
00:35:00,220 --> 00:35:03,960
I told you, I won't work in any medical-related field anymore.

451
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:06,920
You signed this non-disclosure agreement, right?

452
00:35:09,060 --> 00:35:10,760
So what?

453
00:35:10,760 --> 00:35:15,920
As a medical school professor, aren't you afraid of me exposing you for hiring a translator?

454
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:18,960
That's why I need you to sign a non-disclosure agreement.

455
00:35:20,380 --> 00:35:23,300
If you breach the contract, you'll have to pay a penalty.

456
00:35:24,780 --> 00:35:26,520
Don't you still have to interview me?

457
00:35:26,520 --> 00:35:29,680
If I fail the interview, I guess Party A will initiate contract termination.

458
00:35:29,680 --> 00:35:34,460
Congratulations, Student Su. You've successfully passed the interview.

459
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:39,480
You've read through all the terms of this agreement carefully, right?

460
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:43,200
After Party B receives the deposit and passes the interview,

461
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:46,000
if Party B breaches the contract or fails to fulfill the job responsibilities,

462
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:51,005
they will be required to pay Party A a penalty of ten times the deposit.

463
00:35:51,005 --> 00:35:53,590
But I didn't receive your deposit,

464
00:35:54,400 --> 00:35:56,700
so this breach of contract clause isn't valid.

465
00:36:00,380 --> 00:36:01,720

466
00:36:08,960 --> 00:36:10,480

467
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:15,180
Report to the lab on the third floor at 8 a.m. tomorrow morning.

468
00:36:15,180 --> 00:36:19,040
There will be a 50 RMB  (7.04 USD)  fine for every minute you're late, with no upper limit.

469
00:36:19,040 --> 00:36:21,040
You must clock in every day you work.

470
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:22,600
Any work-related information

471
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:27,200
and any details about staff cannot be disclosed to outsiders and must be kept confidential.

472
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:29,240
And here's the last but most important point.

473
00:36:29,240 --> 00:36:33,780
Without my permission, you cannot allow anyone to enter the lab.

474
00:36:41,020 --> 00:36:45,440

475
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:47,480

476
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:52,620
Pleasure working with you, Student Su.

477
00:37:01,560 --> 00:37:04,160
How can you just push me around like this?

478
00:37:05,100 --> 00:37:08,920
 Jiang Muying, I'll give you half an hour to show up at my place.

479
00:37:08,920 --> 00:37:14,300
Otherwise, the video of you snoring in your sleep will appear in My Moments feed.

480
00:37:21,540 --> 00:37:25,200
Wei'an, I don't even need half an hour. I can be here in half a minute.

481
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:28,940
Congratulations, Interpreter Su! You've returned with a victory.

482
00:37:34,200 --> 00:37:37,680
What? Is making money not good enough for you?

483
00:37:37,680 --> 00:37:39,360
You already know the answer.

484
00:37:39,360 --> 00:37:40,480
Are you angry?

485
00:37:40,480 --> 00:37:41,880
Jiang Muying,

486
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:44,760
what benefits did Gu Yunzheng offer you to make you turn against me?

487
00:37:44,760 --> 00:37:46,200
I didn't!

488
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:48,300
I never turned against you.

489
00:37:48,300 --> 00:37:51,740
The unfair contract you made me sign has put me in trouble.

490
00:37:51,740 --> 00:37:53,440
That's enough, Wei'an.

491
00:37:53,440 --> 00:37:55,800
Stop making a fuss. You've already signed it.

492
00:37:55,800 --> 00:37:59,100
Also, while it's said that people shouldn't compromise for just a bit of money,

493
00:37:59,100 --> 00:38:01,940
this is a lot of money. Just think about it!

494
00:38:01,940 --> 00:38:07,040
If I were as capable as you, I would have eagerly signed this unfair contract myself.

495
00:38:07,040 --> 00:38:09,640
Why can't you understand me?

496
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:14,200
I don't want to get close to Gu Yunzheng anymore.

497
00:38:15,200 --> 00:38:18,760
Are you still unable to let go of him?

498
00:38:19,800 --> 00:38:21,780
I find him unpleasant.

499
00:38:21,780 --> 00:38:23,740
I think he's arrogant and obnoxious.

500
00:38:23,740 --> 00:38:26,080
That's right. It's good that you dislike him.

501
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:28,800
I was worried that you liked him, so now I feel relieved.

502
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:33,400
Let me tell you, I heard that Li Wantong has already made her move

503
00:38:33,400 --> 00:38:37,260
and officially won over Dr. Gu. She's his official girlfriend now.

504
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:40,240
Don't worry.

505
00:38:40,240 --> 00:38:42,240
Dr. Gu has gotten over you already.

506
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:45,800
